Understanding pthread synchronization mechanisms - mutexes, CVs and semaphores. 

Que 2: 
taskqueue.c 
Main thread reads the number of worker threads as CLI 
Main thread reads the tasks one by one and enters the task into a queue
A free thread from the thread pool picks up the task and processes it. 
Once all task are complete, the main thread joins the other threads and the global variables are printed. 
Once all tasks are complete, the main thread prints the global vars
